SIMPLE: topple
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topple
<hw>Top"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Toppled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Toppling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From <er>Top</er>
summit.]</ety> <def>To fall forward; to pitch or tumble down.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though castles <qex>topple</qex> on their warders' heads.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Topple
<hw>Top"ple</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To throw down; to
overturn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>topple</qex> crags from the precipice.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top-proud</ent>⟦br⟧
